></sup></b></p>
<p dir=3D"ltr"><span>Once you have got the rank you compute the difference =
in the ranks. So, in this case, the difference in the rank for the first da=
ta point is 2 and we square it, similarly, we take the difference in the se=
cond data point in the ranks between X</span><sub><span>i</span></sub><span=
> and Y</span><sub><span>i</span></sub><span> which is 2, and square it and=
