<h3><b><strong>Properties Of Spearman Correlation</strong></b></h3><ul><li =
value=3D"1"><span>r</span><sub><span>s</span></sub><span> takes a value bet=
ween -1(negative association) and 1(positive association).</span></li><li v=
alue=3D"2"><span>r</span><sub><span>s</span></sub><span> =3D 0 means no ass=
ociation.</span></li><li value=3D"3"><span>It can be used when the associat=
ion is not linear.</span></li><li value=3D"4"><span>It can be applied to or=
dinal variables.</span></li></ul><h3><span>Monotonic and Non-monotonic rela=
tionships</span></h3><p dir=3D"ltr"><span>A monotonic relationship is a mat=
hematical relationship between two variables where the direction of the rel=
ationship (increase or decrease) remains consistent.</span></p>
<p dir=3D"ltr"><span>A non-monotonic relationship is a mathematical relatio=
nship between two variables where the direction of the relationship is not =
consistently increasing or decreasing.</span></p>
